<section id='sec-6' class='block'>
<div class='act'><span class='act-num'>— Scene VI</span><span class='act-sep'></span><span class='act-tag'>Artifact 06</span></div><h1 class='sec-h1'><span>Solution Design</span> <em class='brass'>(Marcus — Solution Architect)</em></h1>
<p>The target architecture: data model, security, automation, integrations, UI. This is the longest section of the SDS — Marcus must produce this in enough detail for BUILD agents (Diego/Zara) to implement without inventing missing pieces.</p>
<p class='note'>This section is the primary input to all BUILD-phase agents. Every gap or vagueness here translates into improvisation by Diego (Apex), Zara (LWC), Raj (Admin) and Jordan (DevOps).</p>
<h2 id='sub-6-1' class='sec-h2'><span>6.1 Data Model</span> <em class='brass'>Entity Relationship Diagram</em></h2>
<p>The target data model has {{ data_model.standard_objects | length }} standard objects extended, {{ data_model.custom_objects | length }} new custom objects, and {{ data_model.relationships | length }} relationships.</p>
<div class='figure-block'><div class='figure-caption'>Figure 1 — Target ERD ({{ data_model.custom_objects | length }} custom objects, {{ data_model.relationships | length }} relationships) — generated from Marcus<strong>'</strong>s erd_mermaid block</div>
<div class='mermaid-wrap'><pre class="mermaid">
{{ data_model.erd_mermaid }}
</pre></div>
</div>
<h2 id='sub-6-2' class='sec-h2'><span>6.2 Custom Objects</span> <em class='brass'>({{ data_model.custom_objects | length }})</em></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>API name</strong></th>
<th><strong>Sharing</strong></th>
<th><strong>Purpose</strong></th>
<th><strong># Fields</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for obj in data_model.custom_objects %}<tr>
<td><strong>{{ obj.api_name }}</strong></td>
<td>{{ obj.sharing_model }}</td>
<td>{{ obj.purpose }}</td>
<td><strong>{{ obj.fields | length }}</strong></td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}</tbody></table>
<h2 id='sub-6-3' class='sec-h2'><span>6.3 Custom Object</span> <em class='brass'>Field Details</em></h2>
{% for obj in data_model.custom_objects %}<p><strong>{{ obj.api_name }}  </strong>({{ obj.label }}) — {{ obj.fields | length }} fields</p>
<p class='note'>{{ obj.purpose }}</p>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>API name</strong></th>
<th><strong>Type</strong></th>
<th><strong>Req?</strong></th>
<th><strong>Description</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for field in obj.fields %}<tr>
<td><strong>{{ field.api_name }}</strong></td>
<td>{{ field.type }}</td>
<td>{% if field.required %}<strong>✓</strong>{% endif %}</td>
<td>{{ field.description }}</td>
</tr>
{% if 'values' in field %}<tr>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td><strong>Picklist values: </strong><em>{{ field['values'] | join(', ') }}</em></td>
</tr>
{% endif %}{% endfor %}</tbody></table>
{% endfor %}<h2 id='sub-6-4' class='sec-h2'><span>6.4 Relationships</span> <em class='brass'>({{ data_model.relationships | length }})</em></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Parent</strong></th>
<th><strong>Child</strong></th>
<th><strong>Type</strong></th>
<th><strong>Field</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for rel in data_model.relationships %}<tr>
<td><strong>{{ rel.from }}</strong></td>
<td><strong>{{ rel.to }}</strong></td>
<td>{{ rel.type }}</td>
<td>{{ rel.field }}</td>
</tr>
{% endfor %}</tbody></table>
